{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Baxter Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Baxter Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Victoria Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|76|40|S|161|51|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Fry Glacier]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Baxter Glacier''' ({{Coord|76|40|S|161|51|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] nurtured by icefalls from [[Flight Deck Neve]], flowing northeast between [[Flagship Mountain]] and [[Mount Davidson (Antarctica)|Mount Davidson]] to enter [[Fry Glacier]], in [[Convoy Range]], [[Victoria Land]]. It was named by a 1976–77 [[Victoria University of Wellington Antarctic Expedition]] (VUWAE) field party after [[James K. Baxter]], [[New Zealand]] poet and social critic.
==See also== * [[List of glaciers in the Antarctic]] * [[Glaciology]]
