{{primary sources|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox Organization |name = International Association for Social Science Information Services and Technology |image = File:Iassist logo 2016 1.png |image_border = |size = 250px |caption = IASSIST Logo |abbreviation = IASSIST |motto = |formation = {{start date and age|1974}} |extinction = |type = [[Non-profit organization|Non-profit]] |status = |purpose = "IASSIST is an international organization of professionals working with information technology and data services to support research and teaching in the social sciences."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iassistdata.org |title=IASSIST home page |publisher=IASSIST |access-date=2016-05-30 }}</ref> |region_served = Worldwide |membership = ~450<ref name="about">{{cite web |url=http://www.iassistdata.org/about/index.html |title=About IASSIST |publisher=IASSIST |access-date=2016-05-30 }}</ref> |language = |leader_title = [[President]] |leader_name = [[Tuomas J. Alaterä]] |main_organ = |num_volunteers = 21 (voting members) |website = [http://www.iassistdata.org/ IASSIST] |remarks = }}
The '''International Association for Social Science Information Services and Technology''' (or IASSIST) is an international organisation that provides professional development, communication and conferences for data librarians, archivists, and social science aligned information specialists. <ref name="about"/> Each year the IASSIST Fellow program sponsors members from developing nations to attend events and professional development to further the advancement of information management. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iassistdata.org/blog/iassist-fellows-program-2015-16 |title=IASSIST Fellowship Blog |publisher=IASSIST |access-date=2016-05-30 }}</ref>
