[[Category:Social sciences]]

{{Sky|08|13|58.77|+|45|44|41.9}} {{Infobox galaxy | name = IC 2233 | image = The Needle Galaxy.jpg | image_size = 300px | caption = The spiral galaxy IC 2233 is one of the flattest galaxies known. | credit = ESA/Hubble & NASA Acknowledgement: Luca Limatola | epoch = [[J2000]] | pronounce = | constellation name = [[Lynx (constellation)|Lynx]] | ra = {{RA|08|13|58.77}}<ref name=simbad>{{cite web|title=SIMBAD basic query result|url=http://simbad.u-strasbg.fr/simbad/sim-basic?Ident=IC+2233|work=Astronomical Database|publisher=SIMBAD|accessdate=13 February 2013}}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|+45|44|41.9}}<ref name=simbad/> | z = 0.001868<ref name=simbad/> | h_radial_v = 559 km/s<ref name=simbad/> | gal_v = | dist_ly = 40 million light-years<ref name="esa/hubble">{{cite news|title=The Needle Galaxy|url=http://www.spacetelescope.org/images/potw1251a/|accessdate=13 February 2013|newspaper=ESA/Hubble Picture of the Week}}</ref> | group_cluster = | type = Sd D<ref name=simbad/> | mass = <!-- In solar masses --> | mass_light_ratio = <!-- In solar units --> | stars = | appmag_v = 12.63<ref name=simbad/> | absmag_v = | size_v = | notes = | names = 2MASX J08135890+4544317, SDSS J081358.76+454441.8, Z 236-36, FGC 730, 2MASXI J0813589+454434, SHOC 192, Z 0810.4+4554, IRAS F08104+4553, MCG+08-15-052, TC 702, [M98c] 081027.6+455350, LCSB L334, 2MFGC 6519, UGC 4278, LEDA 23071, RFGC 1340, UZC J081358.9+454434 | references = }}
'''IC 2233''', also known as '''UGC 4278''', is a [[spiral galaxy]] lying in the constellation of [[Lynx (constellation)|Lynx]]. IC 2233 is located between 26 and 40 million light-years away from [[Earth]]. A comparatively quiet galaxy with a low rate of star formation (less than one solar mass every twenty years), it was long thought to be possibly interacting with the [[NGC 2537|Bear's Paw galaxy]]. However, this is now considered highly unlikely as [[Radio astronomy|radio]] observations with the [[Karl G. Jansky Very Large Array|Very Large Array]] showed the two galaxies lie at different distances.<ref name="Matthews 2007">{{cite journal|author1=Matthews, Lynn D. |author2=Uson, Juan M. |date=2007|title=H I Imaging Observations of Superthin Galaxies. II. IC 2233 and the Blue Compact Dwarf NGC 2537.|journal=The Astronomical Journal|volume=135|issue=1|pages=291|doi=10.1088/0004-6256/135/1/291|arxiv = 0709.4249 |bibcode = 2008AJ....135..291M }}</ref> This galaxy was discovered by British astronomer [[Isaac Roberts]] in 1894.
