{{For|the football player|Luigi Luciani (footballer)}} [[File:Luigi Luciani.jpg|right|thumb|<center>Luigi Luciani]] '''Luigi Luciani''' [[Fellow of the Royal Society|ForMemRS]] (23 November 1842, in [[Ascoli Piceno]] – 23 June 1919) was an Italian [[neuroscientist]].<ref>http://www.ibro.org/Pub/Pub_Main_Display.asp?LC_Docs_ID=3476</ref> He also contributed to [[Karel Frederik Wenckebach]]'s work on what is now known as [[second-degree atrioventricular block]] of the heart in which Wenckebach described the periodicity of this block as "Luciani periodicity." <ref>{{cite journal|last1=Silverman|first1=Mark E|title=Woldemar Mobitz and His 1924 Classification of Second-Degree Atrioventricular Block|journal=Circulation|date=30 August 2004|volume=110|pages=1162–7|doi=10.1161/01.CIR.0000140669.35049.34|pmid=15339865}}</ref>
