'''Vandika Ervandovna Avetisyan''' (born October 5, 1928) is a Doctor of Biology and a noted [[Armenians|Armenian]] [[botanist]] and [[mycologist]]. She has worked and explored extensively in her native [[Armenia]] under the auspices of the Institute of Botany of the [[Armenian National Academy of Sciences]]. Her alma mater is [[Yerevan State University]], the oldest and most prestigious of [[List of universities in Yerevan|Yerevan's universities]]. {{botanist|V.E.Avet.|inline=yes}}.<ref>Brummitt, R.K. and Powell, C.E. ''Authors of plant names: a list of authors of scientific names of plants, with recommended standard forms of their names, including abbreviations''. New edition Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, 1991. 732 pages {{ISBN|0-947643-44-3}} pps.38-39.</ref>
==Alternative Names== Avetissjan, Vanda E. ; Avetisian, Vanda E. ; Avetissian, Vanda E.
